\details{
\subsection{Purpose}{

Retrieves all public market data from Hyperliquid's \verb{/info} endpoint: perp
and spot metadata, asset contexts (mark/mid/oracle/funding/open-interest),
all mids, the L2 order book, OHLCV candles, funding history and predicted
fundings, builder-deployed perp dexes, recent trades, and exchange status.
Every method is unauthenticated and needs no wallet key.

Inherits from \link{HyperliquidBase}. All methods support both synchronous and
asynchronous execution depending on the \code{async} argument at construction; in
async mode each returns a \link[promises:promise]{promises::promise} resolving to the same
\link[data.table:data.table]{data.table::data.table}.

Methods take a \code{coin} as its canonical Hyperliquid symbol (\code{"BTC"}, \code{"@107"},
\code{"PURR/USDC"}). To resolve a friendly name to its canonical coin first, use
the inherited \code{name_to_coin()}.
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\url{https://hyperliquid.gitbook.io/hyperliquid-docs/for-developers/api/info-endpoint}
}

